Title: '⋮' trigger touch target (~20x28px) is below recommended minimum sizes

Finding:
.row-menu-btn has padding: 2px 6px, font-size: 16px, line-height: 1, yielding a tap area of roughly 20px tall by ~28px wide. This is below the WCAG 2.5.8 (AA) 24x24 CSS px minimum target size and well below the 2.5.5 (AAA) / platform 44x44 recommendation, making the already hover-gated trigger hard to hit accurately on touch even once it is made visible. The tappable area should be enlarged.

Fix instructions (follow exactly; make targeted, minimal changes):
In src/app.css, increase the .row-menu-btn hit area to at least 24x24 (preferably ~32px) without changing its visual glyph size. Adjust the .row-menu-btn rule's padding so the box meets the minimum, e.g. set `padding: 6px 8px; min-width: 24px; min-height: 24px;` (keeping font-size: 16px and line-height: 1) and ensure the button is centered in the actions cell (the cell is text-align:right from the existing rule, which is fine). Keep border:none, background:none, border-radius:4px, and the opacity/pointer-events behavior. This is a CSS-only change.

